# QA Report — Sprint M4a: Instagram Slide-1 Cover-Centering + Image-Grid-Cap
<!-- Generated: 2026-05-03 — Adversarial Spec Review (Sonnet R2) -->
<!-- Status: NEEDS WORK — 2 Critical + 4 High + 3 Medium + 2 Low -->

---

## [FAIL] CRITICAL — `HashtagsRow` position and centering in grid-cover: zero implementation guidance

**What is missing:** A1 moves Hashtags from before-Title to after-Grid in the grid-cover layout. A1b provides constant `GRID_TO_HASHTAGS_GAP_GRID_COVER = 48`. A1 specifies `justifyContent: "center"` on Hashtags.

**What the developer will implement incorrectly:** The current `HashtagsRow` component (slide-template.tsx:163–187) has `marginTop: HEADER_TO_HASHTAGS_GAP = 32` hardcoded in its own style and no `justifyContent: "center"`. To move Hashtags after the grid, the developer must either (a) add a `marginTop` prop to `HashtagsRow` and a `centered` prop, or (b) duplicate the component for the grid-cover branch, or (c) render a raw wrapper `<div style={{marginTop: GRID_TO_HASHTAGS_GAP_GRID_COVER, justifyContent: "center", ...}}>` around `HashtagsRow`. The spec does not specify which approach. Without explicit guidance a developer will try rendering `<HashtagsRow hashtags={...} />` after `<ImageGrid />` and expect the constant to apply automatically — it will not. The result is Hashtags appearing with the old 32px top-margin (not 48px) and left-aligned (not centered).

**Fix:** Add to slide-template.tsx Files-to-Change entry: "Modify `HashtagsRow` to accept `marginTop?: number` and `centered?: boolean` props. In grid-cover branch, render `<HashtagsRow marginTop={GRID_TO_HASHTAGS_GAP_GRID_COVER} centered />` after `<ImageGrid />`. In all other branches, call unchanged."

