## [FAIL] CRITICAL — `cells` from `computeSlide1GridSpec` usage never wired into `<ImageGrid>`

**What is missing:** A4b shows:
```ts
const gridSpec = computeSlide1GridSpec(slide.gridImages ?? [], (slide.gridImages ?? []).length);
const cols = gridSpec.columns;
const cells = gridSpec.cells;
```
But the spec never shows the updated `<ImageGrid>` JSX call. Currently the template renders `<ImageGrid cols={gridCols} images={slide.gridImages} .../>`. The spec says to replace `gridCols`, but silently leaves `images` pointing to `slide.gridImages`.

**What the developer will implement incorrectly:** A developer will replace `const gridCols = slide.gridColumns ?? 1` with `gridSpec.columns` and stop there — `cells` is defined but never used. `<ImageGrid images={slide.gridImages} .../>` stays unchanged. This is functionally equivalent post-M4a (because `instagram/route.ts` and the slider are both capped to 4), but:
(1) `instagram/route.ts` before its own M4a update still passes `imageCount` without the `MAX_GRID_IMAGES` clamp → API renders up to `availableImages` images regardless → `slide.gridImages` can be > 4 → `ImageGrid` renders > 4 images without the grid spec.
(2) Codex will flag `cells` as dead code (defined, never read) — P1 finding.
(3) E5 visual smoke test "Grid-Override: images_grid_columns=3 mit imageCount=4 → 2×2" may still pass if `slide.gridImages.length` happens to be 4, but the defense-in-depth logic is absent.

**Fix:** The A4b code snippet must end with the updated JSX: `<ImageGrid cols={gridSpec.columns} images={gridSpec.cells} dataUrls={...} maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER} />`. Spec must explicitly say "`slide.gridImages` is replaced by `gridSpec.cells` in the `<ImageGrid>` call."

