## [FAIL] HIGH — No-grid-Slide-1 centering: `TitleBlock`/`LeadBlock` have no centering mechanism

**What is missing:** A3 says "Title + Lead zentriert (visuelle Konsistenz mit grid-Path-Cover)" for no-grid-Slide-1. Spec A1 specifies `textAlign: "center"` for Title/Lead. But `TitleBlock` (slide-template.tsx:189–217) and `LeadBlock` (219–244) are fixed-format components with no centering prop. The spec does not say how to apply centering.

**What the developer will implement incorrectly:** The developer detects `slide.isFirst && slide.leadOnSlide === true` as the no-grid-cover condition. They need to center Title and Lead but have no prop to flip. They will either add an inline wrapper div with `textAlign: "center"` around the components (which won't work in Satori — Satori requires `textAlign` directly on the text-bearing div, not on a parent, per nextjs-og.md pattern §Rule 2), or they will add a `centered?: boolean` prop to both components. Without explicit guidance they will likely choose the wrong CSS approach and Title/Lead will appear left-aligned despite a code change that looks correct.

**Fix:** Specify in slide-template.tsx Files-to-Change: "Add `centered?: boolean` prop to `TitleBlock` and `LeadBlock`; when `centered`, apply `textAlign: 'center'` directly to the text-bearing `<div>`. In no-grid-cover branch, render both with `centered`. In all other branches, omit (defaults false)."

