## [FAIL] HIGH — No-grid-Slide-1 Hashtags fate is unspecified

**What is missing:** A3 says "nur Title + Lead zentriert" for no-grid-Slide-1. The current `kind === "text"` `isFirst` block (slide-template.tsx:549–567) renders `<HashtagsRow> → <TitleBlock> → <LeadBlock>` — Hashtags appear BEFORE Title, left-aligned.

**What the developer will implement incorrectly:** The spec says to detect no-grid-cover via `isFirst && leadOnSlide === true`. After detection, they center Title and Lead. But `HashtagsRow` is still rendered in the same block, before Title, and the spec never says to remove it, move it, or keep it. A developer who reads "nur Title + Lead zentriert" will assume Hashtags stay as-is (before Title, uncenered) — which is visually inconsistent with the grid-cover where Hashtags are after the grid and centered. The E5 visual smoke for no-grid-path says "Slide 1 = Title + Lead zentriert, Body links-bündig" but makes no assertion about Hashtags position or alignment, so the smoke will not catch this inconsistency.

**Fix:** Add explicit statement to A3: "For no-grid-cover, Hashtags render at their current position (before Title) or are suppressed — document the intended behavior." If Hashtags should be suppressed on no-grid-Slide-1 to match grid-cover aesthetics, state that explicitly and add it to E5.

