## [FAIL] HIGH — A1b `HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER` never connected to `TitleBlock.marginTop`

**What is missing:** A1b defines `HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER = 60` as the gap "between Header and Title" in the new grid-cover layout. Currently `TitleBlock` receives `marginTop={meta.hashtags.length > 0 ? HASHTAGS_TO_TITLE_GAP : HEADER_TO_BODY_GAP}` — this is the hashtag-conditional logic. In the new grid-cover layout, Hashtags have moved below the grid, so the TitleBlock marginTop should be `HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER = 60` unconditionally. The spec never says "use `HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER` as `TitleBlock.marginTop` in the grid-cover branch".

**What the developer will implement incorrectly:** A developer adds the new constants A1b, moves Hashtags below the grid, and leaves `TitleBlock.marginTop` using the old conditional logic. If the event HAS hashtags, `marginTop = HASHTAGS_TO_TITLE_GAP = 60` (accidentally correct value), but the condition fires because `meta.hashtags.length > 0` which is now logically stale. If the event has NO hashtags, `marginTop = HEADER_TO_BODY_GAP = 60` (also coincidentally correct, since both constants are 60). So the pixel result is accidentally correct today — but the logic is wrong and fragile. Codex will flag this as stale conditional logic referencing hashtags that are no longer adjacent to the title in this branch.

**Fix:** Add explicit statement to slide-template.tsx Files-to-Change entry: "In grid-cover branch, `TitleBlock.marginTop = HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER` (not the hashtag-conditional)."

