## [FAIL] LOW — `HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER` naming collision risk with existing `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP = 18`

**What is missing:** A1b defines `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP_GRID_COVER = 32` (new). There exists a `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP = 18` (current). Spec says existing constants "werden NICHT modifiziert". But the SlideTemplate currently uses `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP` (18px) for text-slides with lead. A developer reading "TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP_GRID_COVER = 32 for grid-cover" might also accidentally replace `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP` in the no-grid text path with 32px, changing existing slide spacing.

**Fix:** Add explicit note: "`TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP = 18` is used exclusively in the `kind === 'text'` `isFirst` branch (no-grid-path). `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP_GRID_COVER = 32` is used exclusively in the `kind === 'grid'` branch. Do NOT modify the text-path usage."

---

## Verdict

**NEEDS WORK**

2 Critical + 4 High + 3 Medium + 2 Low findings. The spec has well-specified algorithmic requirements (A2b budget fix, A3b leadOnSlide override, A4 grid-spec mapping, A6 clamp) but is systematically incomplete for the visual rendering implementation in `slide-template.tsx`: it specifies WHAT to render but not HOW to implement the centering and repositioning using the existing component primitives. A developer implementing exactly what is written will produce layout bugs in grid-cover (wrong Hashtag position/alignment, wrong Title gap), miss the `cells` wiring to `<ImageGrid>`, and fail the E4 PUT validator test. The `isOrphan` dead-code issue will cause a Codex R1 [P1-P2] finding. Address the 2 Critical and 4 High findings before implementation.
